logical innovation, and economic power into a queer space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCivil rights -- United States -- History. 0aCivil rightszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aFlight attendants -- Labor unions -- United States. 0aFlight attendants -- United States -- History. 0aFlight attendantsxLabor unionszUnited States. 0aFlight attendantszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aGays -- Employment -- United States. 0aGaysxEmploymentzUnited States. 0aSexual orientation -- United States. 0aSexual orientationzUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a1964 civil rights act.  a20th century.  aaids phobia.  aair transport.  acareer.  acivil rights.  aengaging.  aflight.  aflying.  agay men.  agender studies.  ahistorical.  ahistory of lgbt.  ahistory.  ahiv aids.  ahomophobia.  ahomosexual panic.  alabor.  algbt business.  algbt history.  algbt interest.  algbt.  algbtqia.  alively.  amale flight attendants.  apage turner.  apilots.  apolitical.  aqueer books.  aqueer studies.  aqueer.  asex and gender.  asex and sexuality.  asocial issues.  asocial justice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095530140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520955301/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles